HEADWORD: Emotionalize
<hw>E*mo"tion*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To give an
emotional character to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brought up in a pious family where religion was not talked about
<qex>emotionalized</qex>, but was accepted as the rule of thought and
conduct.</q> <rj><qau>Froude.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emotioned</ent>⟦br⟧
